\par Even in the period when Darwin wrote }{\i\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8277579\charrsid6891576 The Origin of Species}{\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8277579\charrsid6891576 , the belief that bacteria could come into existen
ce from non-living matter was widely accepted in the world of science. 
\par However, five years after Darwin's book was published, the discovery of Louis Pasteur disproved this belief, which constituted the groundwork of evolution. Pasteur summarized the conclusion he reached after time-consuming studies and experiments: }{
\i\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8277579\charrsid6891576 "The claim that inanimate matter can originate life is buried in history for good."}{\f0\fs18\up6\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8277579\charrsid6891576 17}{
